<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="376" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 339.41/5.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">British Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Chargé d’affaires</hi>: I beg to
                            acknowledge the receipt of your personal note of the 17th ultimo, in
                            further relation to the <pb facs="0380" n="264" xml:id="pg_264"/>
                            protection of foreign life and property in the Dominican Republic.</p>
                        <p>In reply I beg to advise you that, on June 24 last, the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Marietta</hi> arrived at Sanchez, and that she has
                            instructions to report on conditions in the Dominican Republic, with
                            special reference to the protection of foreign lives and property.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>